    "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
    "body": "Strong concept ACK on providing a REST API which is built with the intention to be secure.\r\n\r\nThe current situation where we don't want to vouch for the security of our REST API and instead suggest that our users should roll their own sanitisation via an `nginx` proxy if they want to use it in settings where security might be needed feels really weird for a security critical project. We can do better! :)",
